Quote: The Labour Party tried to carry on the radical liberal ideal with regard to land by advocating a tenure known as `usehold' (their opponents called it `loosehold') but soon discovered that it was a liability. No one could hope to woo the rural voters without acknowledging their true god whose name was Private Property.
